		<outline text="May 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="may2021" >
			<outline text="May 7" type="calendarDay" name="07" >
				<outline text="This is a high-impact decision. 

Some devs need to use Win x86-only apps (in our case IAR Embedded Workbench for ARM) while also needing to use Xcode.

Other than carrying two laptops, have others had thoughts as to how the cross-platform dev community might cope?

@siracusa? &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/VMwareFusion/status/1387900548779679745&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 07 May 2021 21:57:16 GMT" tweetId="1390787844512260097" urltweet="https://twitter.com/rozzie/status/1390787844512260097" tweetUserName="rozzie" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
		<outline text="July 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="july2021" >
			<outline text="July 13" type="calendarDay" name="13" >
				<outline text="Hey @natfriedman, this is not unrelated to what we'd discussed some time back. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1414945524101287938&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2021 15:45:28 GMT" tweetId="1414974265787654154" urltweet="https://twitter.com/rozzie/status/1414974265787654154" tweetUserName="rozzie" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 12" type="calendarDay" name="12" >
				<outline text="Very pleased to announce that our @blueswireless Series A round was led by @sequoia and @lachygroom, joined by @xyz_vc and returning investor BMGI.

A strongly product-led developer-focused company, working with tremendous commercial customers. Join us!

&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.geekwire.com/2021/ray-ozzies-telecom-startup-blues-wireless-raises-22m-bill-gates-others/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 14:47:22 GMT" tweetId="1414597256586711048" urltweet="https://twitter.com/rozzie/status/1414597256586711048" tweetUserName="rozzie" >
					<outline text="Thanks, @inafried 

&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.axios.com/ray-ozzie-blues-wireless-5g-funding-5dd3b9d2-f16e-4e27-a0c8-d01ca99518ff.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 15:00:11 GMT" tweetId="1414600483679862791" urltweet="https://twitter.com/rozzie/status/1414600483679862791" inReplyToId="1414597256586711048" tweetUserName="rozzie" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			</outline>
		<outline text="April 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="april2021" >
